    {
      "id": "net-working-capital-walkthrough",
      "title": "Net Working Capital Walkthrough",
      "intent": "risk",
      "content": "- Risk: DSO expansion in Q2 inflates reported working capital need.\n- Risk: AP timing normalization may reduce temporary cash benefit in H2.\n- Risk: settlement receivable volatility can distort month-end liquidity view.\n- Mitigation: implement weekly receivables intervention for top 20 aging accounts.\n- Mitigation: align payment scheduling policy with vendor criticality tiers.\n- Mitigation: add liquidity trigger thresholds tied to DSO and conversion rates.",
